		<div id="comment_body_64341395">They have been around for years.  Generally, they are either very expensive, have poor physical properties, or break down in use.  They often do not biodegrade under typical conditions either.  Recognizable food and paper items that are many years old can be found in a typical dump, because they do not degrade in the absence of oxygen.  If you want a simple clean recyclable container use glass.  Also, glass bottles can be washed and reused.  This use to be standard practice.</div>
	</div>

