	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64341723"><p>I don't believe a word of this. Maybe you can make a biodegradable plastic, but it comes down to the usual dilemma: Strong, cheap, biodegradable. Pick two.</p><p>This has already been done with Pela phone cases and their copycats. They've been tested and they're simply not biodegradable by any reasonable standard--if at all. The real solution is to reduce consumption, and these companies simply offer a band-aid solution that not only doesn't work, but encourages more consumption under the mistaken belief that it's<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
